{"TopicId":219300,"ForumId":144,"TopicTitle":"Deleting Struts While in Symmetry Just Removes the One Being Held, the Others Remain","CreatedByName":"Spicat","CreatedById":228085,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-09-04T22:14:47Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Spicat","CreatedById":228085,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-09-04T22:14:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EReported Version:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0v0.1.4 (latest) |\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EMods:\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003Enone | \u003Cstrong\u003ECan replicate without mods?\u003C/strong\u003E Yes\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOS:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Windows 10 | \u003Cstrong\u003ECPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Intel(R) Core(TM) i7-10700 CPU @ 2.90GHz | \u003Cstrong\u003EGPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0NVIDIA GeForce RTX 2070 | \u003Cstrong\u003ERAM\u003Cspan\u003E:\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E16GB\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:20px;\u0022\u003ESteps to Replicate:\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Col\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nPlace one part\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nUse symmetry (Every symmetry work (except 1))\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nPlace struts on the part\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nDelete it, either with the \u0022Del\u0022 key or with the \u0022bin\u0022 at the bottom of\u00A0the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003Evab\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E menu\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ol\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EIncluded Attachments:\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cvideo class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 controls=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.global.core.embeddedvideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Csource type=\u0022video/mp4\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/monthly_2023_11/2023-09-0423-54-27.mp4.8baf810c2d9a36a544e9527f3eae34d9.mp4\u0022\u003E\u003Ca class=\u0022ipsAttachLink\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/applications/core/interface/file/attachment.php?id=991\u0026amp;key=45e8ad9fcb73f3b29928c11911c3c9f6\u0022 data-fileid=\u0022991\u0022 data-fileext=\u0022mp4\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E2023-09-0423-54-27.mp4\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/video\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-11-01T18:12:45Z\u0022 title=\u002211/01/2023 06:12  PM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Nov 1\u0022\u003ENovember 1, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Spicat\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spicat","CreatedById":228085,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-02-03T22:56:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStill present in 0.2.1.0.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mushylog","CreatedById":227298,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-11-01T18:33:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes! Great post, this bug is particularly bothersome\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Scarecrow71","CreatedById":210112,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-02-05T19:25:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI can confirm that this also happens with Fuel Lines, not just Struts.\u00A0 I think there are similarities between these two parts, so the same bug affects both.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Flush Foot","CreatedById":193460,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-02-06T18:53:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have also had to do the \u201Chunt around for leftover nodes\u201D after removing symmetried struts/fuel lines.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(Edit: found the \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/topic/219297-struts-in-symmetry-dont-connect-correctly-when-2-inline-parts-are-facing-awaytowards-each-other/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003Erelevant report here\u003C/a\u003E) Probably not relevant here, but another symmetry \u0026amp; strut-behaviour I dislike is when you go straight down from an upside-down slanted tank/piece to one that is right-side up below it (to strut two stages together, for example) and the struts try to cross through the middle of the parts as if looking for the matching X-Y-Z coordinates on the other part, despite them being in opposite orientations.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222024-02-06T18:56:39Z\u0022 title=\u002202/06/2024 06:56  PM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Feb 6\u0022\u003EFebruary 6\u003C/time\u003E by Flush Foot\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}